HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1205
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Sam Wofford upon his
receipt of the Professional Staff of the Year
Award.
WHEREAS, our nation was conceived by individuals who were willing to sacrifice their
personal concerns to ensure the public safety and welfare, and the Volunteer State is especially
proud to be the home of so many valiant individuals who have performed above and beyond the
call of duty in service of public safety; and
WHEREAS, Sam Wofford was recently honored with the Chattanooga Police
Department's (CPD's) Professional Staff of the Year Award in recognition of his exceptional
performance, dedication, and commitment as an RTIC Technician and IT Specialist for the
department; and
WHEREAS, Sam Wofford consistently exceeds expectations, approaching every task
with a positive, helpful, and approachable demeanor that fosters collaboration; and
WHEREAS, regardless of the challenge, he is the first to volunteer his time and
expertise; his off-call reliability makes Mr. Wofford an IT Unit cornerstone and a trusted partner;
and
WHEREAS, Sam Wofford quickly and effectively troubleshoots complex technical
issues, often preemptively solving problems; his calm problem-solving ensures critical systems
remain operational and staff duties uninterrupted; and
WHEREAS, beyond his technical skill, Sam Wofford is distinguished by his humility and
professionalism, loyally supporting CPD and his colleagues without seeking recognition; and
WHEREAS, Sam Wofford has made a lasting impact on the Chattanooga Police
Department; now, therefore,
HJR1205
016028
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Sam Wofford upon his receipt of the Professional
Staff of the Year Award from the Chattanooga Police Department.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
